<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,922,1628]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1442,1468]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[336,485,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dealbatus">
<emphasis box="[336,485,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">P. dealbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from Indian species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melichar" authorityYear="1903" box="[884,999,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[884,999,1443,1468]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Pythamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lacking lateral processes to the aedeagal shaft. Externally it resembles both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2007" box="[673,827,1483,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis box="[673,827,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">P. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2007" box="[885,1029,1483,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis box="[885,1029,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">P. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has a larger yellow spot at the base of the median keel on the vertex. It shares the straighter ventral pygophore process with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2007" box="[1276,1429,1523,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biramosus">
<emphasis box="[1276,1429,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">P. biramosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is the only species known from 
<collectingCountry box="[587,707,1562,1588]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. The synonymy of 
<taxonomicName box="[934,1078,1563,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dealbatus">
<emphasis box="[934,1078,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">P. dealbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1908" box="[1136,1296,1563,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Dussana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quaerenda">
<emphasis box="[1136,1296,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">D. quaerenda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on the examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[421,483,1602,1628]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">types</typeStatus>
of these two species.
</paragraph>
